qas.question: When was the National Government of China moved to Chungking?

answers.text: A few days before the fall of the city

qas.question: When was the Nanjing Regime established?
Who was the leader of the Nanjing Regime?
When did the KMT move back to Nanjing?
What was another name for the Nanjing Regime?

context: <a0_0>A few days before the fall of the city<a0_0/>, the National Government of China was relocated to the southwestern city Chungking (Chongqing) and resumed Chinese resistance. In <a1_0>1940<a1_0/>, a Japanese-collaborationist government known as the "Nanjing Regime" or <a4_0>"Reorganized National Government of China"<a4_0/> led by <a2_0>Wang Jingwei<a2_0/> was established in Nanjing as a rival to Chiang Kai-shek's government in Chongqing. In <a3_0>1946<a3_0/>, after the Surrender of Japan, the KMT relocated its central government back to Nanjing.
